# .cursorrules (place in axis_reliability/ directory)

This is a ROS 2 Humble project using Python 3.10.

CRITICAL RULES:
- Only use APIs that exist in ROS 2 Humble documentation: https://docs.ros.org/en/humble/
- Before using any message type, verify it exists at: https://docs.ros.org/en/humble/p/[package]/
- sensor_msgs/NavSatFix does NOT have an hdop field (it has position_covariance)
- Use tf_transformations for quaternion math, not tf2 (Python binding differences)
- Time arithmetic: (Time - Time).nanoseconds returns int64, divide by 1e9 for seconds

STYLE:
- Add type hints to all function signatures
- Use rclpy.node.Node as base class
- Log with self.get_logger().info/warn/error
- Parameters must be declared with self.declare_parameter() before use

VERIFICATION:
- If unsure about any ROS 2 API, state: "VERIFY: [method] in [package]"
- Never invent field names or methods
- Prefer verbose, explicit code over clever shortcuts